- Rewrite entirely to match `print_checks` verbatim: `printf '🟢/🟡/🔴'` traffic-light output, same per-tool conditionals (brew, starship, pyenv, python3, nano, tmux), same formatting
- Accept `VERBOSE` env var for consistency with installer context
- `install.sh`: delete `print_checks` function body, replace call site with `bash [REPO_DIR}/scripts/post-install-checks.sh`

### `scripts/setup-starship.sh` → replaces `configure_starship_prompt` in `install.sh`
- Rewrite to match `configure_starship_prompt` exactly: accept `PRESERVE`, `DRY_RUN`, `VERBOSE`, `SKEL_DIR`, `SKEL_PROFILE` as env vars
- Replicate the same `backup_path`/`copy_item` logic inline in the script (small, self-contained helpers)
- Same fallback chain: `starship preset tokyo-night`, then skel file, then warn
- `install.sh`: delete `configure_starship_prompt` function body, replace call site with env-var-prefixed `bash [REPO_DIR}/scripts/setup-starship.sh`

### `scripts/setup-pyenv.sh` → delete
- Fully redundant with `packages.yaml` brew installs — pyenv and pyenv-virtualenv are already in the brew package list

**Files:** `install.sh`, `scripts/post-install-checks.sh`, `scripts/setup-starship.sh`, `scripts/setup-pyenv.sh`

